# dotfiles-Gentoo/gentoo/package.accept_keywords.example
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# On a STABLE profile, fast-moving Rust CLI tools sometimes only have ~amd64
# (testing) keywords, so emerge refuses them with a "masked by: ~amd64 keyword"
# message. This file unmasks just those packages — REVIEW first, then copy the
# lines you actually need into /etc/portage/package.accept_keywords/ (file or dir).
#
# DON'T blanket-unmask. Check what a given atom needs first:
#   emerge -p <category/name>      # shows the exact keyword/USE that's blocking
#
# Replace ~amd64 with your arch keyword if you're not on amd64 (e.g. ~arm64).
# Whether each line is needed depends on your profile + tree state on the day —
# several of these may already be stable for you, in which case skip them.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# sys-apps/eza ~amd64
# app-shells/atuin ~amd64
# app-misc/yazi ~amd64
# app-misc/tealdeer ~amd64
# dev-vcs/lazygit ~amd64
# app-shells/starship ~amd64
